This paper is focused on investigating the challenges faced by software developers when embedding privacy into software designs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) which deals with privacy and security issues in computer systems. The paper also involves software design tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of user privacy, which could place it in the category of cs.CY (Computers and Society). The study involves human participants, which could also make it relevant to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper provides recommendations to address the problems faced by developers, which could place it in the category of cs.PR (Performance and Reliability).
